{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Resolve Decap CMS External Media Library Error on GitHub Pages\n\nFix the \"Missing external media library 'default'\" error that prevents Decap CMS from functioning correctly when deployed to GitHub Pages.\n\nRequirements:\n- Locate the CMS initialization code (typically in admin/index.html or a dedicated CMS setup file)\n- Verify that the media library is properly registered using 'registerMediaLibrary' before CMS initialization\n- Ensure the registration occurs before 'CMS.init()' is called\n- Confirm the media library configuration in config.yml matches the registered library name\n- Test CMS functionality locally before deploying\n- Deploy to GitHub Pages and verify the CMS loads without configuration errors\n- Ensure image/media upload and management features work correctly\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Check if the media library registration code is being properly bundled for production\n- Verify asset paths are correct for GitHub Pages subdirectory deployment if applicable\n- Confirm all CMS dependencies are included in the production build\n- Check browser console for any related module loading errors\n\nSuccess criteria:\n- CMS admin interface loads without \"Missing external media library\" error\n- Media library functions correctly (upload, select, delete operations)\n- Configuration validates successfully with no errors in config.yml",
